          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>54638</commentid>
            <who name="Vladimir Kotal">vladimir.kotal</who>
            <bug_when>2009-10-29 13:48:29 +0000</bug_when>
            <thetext>Trying recent build (pre-0.8) I discovered that the History view lists of files touched by given integration, e.g. http://lv-grok1.opensolaris.org:8080/source/history/onnv/onnv-gate/usr/src/lib/libc/port/threads/door_calls.c lists thousands of lines of output, the majority being the first push to OpenSolaris.

The source code lines should not be in the History view by default - firstly, it hangs Firefox nicely, secondly it makes the history view incomprehensible (the other case being files with big number of changes and small numbers of files per change).</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>54733</commentid>
            <who name="Knut Anders Hatlen">knut.hatlen</who>
            <bug_when>2009-10-29 21:54:26 +0000</bug_when>
            <thetext>We should have a way of toggling the display of the file list on or off, with the default being off. Should be fixed before the 0.8 release.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
